title: Super Eagles Players Elect Onazi, Omeruo Assistant Captains
text:
Headlines / Super Eagles Players Elect Onazi, Omeruo Assistant Captains Super Eagles Players Elect Onazi, Omeruo Assistant Captains Headlines , Top Stories 
By James Agberebi: 
Super Eagles players have elected their administrative officers who will assist new skipper, Ahmed Musa, in carrying out his role as leader of the team.‎ 
This was made known on the Super Eagles Twitter handle on Friday. 
The players that were elected are: Ogenyi Onazi as Vice-Captain, Kenneth Omeruo as second Vice-Captain and Efe Ambrose, who will be the team’s spokesperson. Your email address will not be published.
